name=Benoit Allaire&position=goaltending coach&text=Benoit Allaire returns to the Coyotes for his fourth season as the team's goaltending coach. Allaire joined the team in 1997 from Montreal, where he served as goaltending instructor for the Canadiens.

In 1998-99, Coyotes goaltenders had their best showing in franchise history, allowing only 197 goals.

The St. Janvier, Quebec, native also served as a goaltending instructor for six seasons (1989-95) in the Quebec Major Junior Hockey League.
